prompt: Summarize the following story in first person: Here I am again. It seems like there are times when the world decides to dump on me. I always knew that this day would come, but I still wasn't prepared. Three weeks ago I lost my dog. She was my best friend and constant companion. I raised her from a pup, almost like my own child. I know a lot of people scoff when you say that, but I don't care. She was family to me and I miss her so much. She always loved going outside and chasing the ball. Man, was she fast, and great at catching the ball. It was a shock to me when she was no longer able to run around. I knew something was wrong but thought maybe she just had a bug. I took her to the vet and received the worst news I could imagine. Cancer, and she wouldn't make it longer than a week. It's a strange feeling when all you can do is wait for someone to pass on.

choices.text: It's like you're stuck in a time loop and you can't move forward. I have been crying every day since then, sometimes multiple times a day. I feel like I'm drowning in grief. I know it will get better eventually, but for now, it's just too much. I miss her so much.
